    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You run a company that verifies whether wireless mouse receivers are still working.<br><br>Each receiver only listens to a specific frequency determined by the <var>serial</var> of the mouse it was originally paired with. You have a programmable test mouse that can transmit on any frequency.<br><br>Given a mouse serial number, compute the frequency your test mouse must use.<br><br>The frequency is derived from the serial number using the following rules:<br><br>Each character is converted to a numeric value <var>v</var>:<br>Characters 0&ndash;9 &rarr; values 0&ndash;9<br>Characters A&ndash;Z &rarr; values 10&ndash;35<br><br>Initialize an accumulator <var>acc</var>:<br><br><var>acc</var> = <strong>0</strong><br>Process the serial from left to right. For each character with value <var>v</var>:<br><br>If the character is a vowel (<strong>A</strong>, <strong>E</strong>, <strong>I</strong>, <strong>O</strong>, <strong>U</strong>):<br><br><var>acc</var>  = <var>acc</var>  XOR <var>v</var><br><br>Otherwise:<br><br><var>acc</var> = (<var>acc</var> * <const>31</const> + <var>v</var>) mod <const>1000</const><br>The final frequency is <var>acc</var>, formatted as a 3-digit number with leading zeroes if necessary.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The <var>serial</var> of the receiver</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The <var>frequency</var> for your test mouse</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1  &le; length of <var>serial</var>  &le; 100</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">A</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">010</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
